00042 template <typename object_type>
00043 void testObject(const object_type& a)
00044 {
00045     if (os_) *os_ << "testObject(): " << typeid(a).name() << endl;
00046 
00047     // write 'a' out to a stream
00048 
00049     ostringstream oss;
00050     XMLWriter writer(oss);
00051     IO::write(writer, a);
00052     if (os_) *os_ << oss.str() << endl;
00053 
00054     // read 'b' in from stream
00055 
00056     object_type b; 
00057     istringstream iss(oss.str());
00058     IO::read(iss, b);
00059 
00060     // compare 'a' and 'b'
00061 
00062     Diff<object_type> diff(a,b);
00063     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00064     unit_assert(!diff);
00065 }

00399     
00400     a.index = 123;
00401     a.id = "goo";
00402     a.nativeID = "420";
00403     a.defaultArrayLength = 666;
00404     a.dataProcessingPtr = DataProcessingPtr(new DataProcessing("dp"));
00405     a.sourceFilePtr = SourceFilePtr(new SourceFile("sf"));
00406     a.binaryDataArrayPtrs.push_back(BinaryDataArrayPtr(new BinaryDataArray));
00407     for (int i=0; i<100; i++)
00408         a.binaryDataArrayPtrs.back()->data.push_back(i);
00409     a.binaryDataArrayPtrs.push_back(BinaryDataArrayPtr(new BinaryDataArray));
00410     for (int i=0; i<100; i++)
00411         a.binaryDataArrayPtrs.back()->data.push_back(i*2);
00412     a.spectrumDescription.cvParams.push_back(MS_reflectron_on);
00413     a.cvParams.push_back(MS_MSn_spectrum);
00414 
00415     // write 'a' out to a stream
00416 
00417     ostringstream oss;
00418     XMLWriter writer(oss);
00419     IO::write(writer, a);
00420     if (os_) *os_ << oss.str() << endl;
00421 
00422     // read 'b' in from stream
00423 
00424     Spectrum b; 
00425     istringstream iss(oss.str());
00426     IO::read(iss, b, IO::ReadBinaryData);
00427     unit_assert(b.sourceFilePosition == 0); // not -1
00428 
00429     // compare 'a' and 'b'
00430 
00431     Diff<Spectrum> diff(a,b);
00432     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00433     unit_assert(!diff);
00434 
00435     // test IgnoreBinaryData
00436 
00437     Spectrum c;
00438     iss.seekg(0);
00439     IO::read(iss, c); // default = IgnoreBinaryData
00440     unit_assert(c.binaryDataArrayPtrs.empty());
00441     unit_assert(c.sourceFilePosition == 0); // not -1
00442 
00443     a.binaryDataArrayPtrs.clear();
00444     diff(a, c);
00445     unit_assert(!diff);
00446 }

00515 void testRun()
00516 {
00517     if (os_) *os_ << "testRun():\n";
00518 
00519     Run a;
00520     
00521     a.id = "goober";
00522     a.instrumentPtr = InstrumentPtr(new Instrument("instrument"));
00523     a.samplePtr = SamplePtr(new Sample("sample"));
00524     a.startTimeStamp = "20 April 2004 4:20pm";  
00525     a.sourceFilePtrs.push_back(SourceFilePtr(new SourceFile("sf1")));
00526     a.sourceFilePtrs.push_back(SourceFilePtr(new SourceFile("sf2")));
00527 
00528     shared_ptr<SpectrumListSimple> spectrumListSimple(new SpectrumListSimple);
00529 
00530     SpectrumPtr spectrum1(new Spectrum);
00531     spectrum1->id = "goober";
00532     spectrum1->index = 0;
00533     spectrum1->nativeID = "420";
00534     spectrum1->defaultArrayLength = 666;
00535     spectrum1->spectrumDescription.userParams.push_back(UserParam("description1"));
00536 
00537     SpectrumPtr spectrum2(new Spectrum);
00538     spectrum2->id = "raisinet";
00539     spectrum2->index = 1;
00540     spectrum2->nativeID = "421";
00541     spectrum2->defaultArrayLength = 667;
00542     spectrum2->spectrumDescription.userParams.push_back(UserParam("description2"));
00543     
00544     spectrumListSimple->spectra.push_back(spectrum1);
00545     spectrumListSimple->spectra.push_back(spectrum2);
00546 
00547     a.spectrumListPtr = spectrumListSimple;
00548 
00549     // write 'a' out to a stream
00550 
00551     ostringstream oss;
00552     XMLWriter writer(oss);
00553     IO::write(writer, a);
00554     if (os_) *os_ << oss.str() << endl;
00555 
00556     // read 'b' in from stream, ignoring SpectrumList (default)
00557 
00558     Run b;
00559     istringstream iss(oss.str());
00560     IO::read(iss, b, IO::IgnoreSpectrumList); // IO::IgnoreSpectrumList 
00561 
00562     // compare 'a' and 'b'
00563 
00564     Diff<Run> diff(a,b);
00565     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00566     unit_assert(diff);
00567     unit_assert(diff.a_b.spectrumListPtr.get());
00568     unit_assert(diff.a_b.spectrumListPtr->size() == 1);
00569     unit_assert(diff.a_b.spectrumListPtr->spectrum(0)->userParams.size() == 1);
00570 
00571     // read 'c' in from stream, reading SpectrumList
00572 
00573     Run c; 
00574     iss.seekg(0);
00575     IO::read(iss, c, IO::ReadSpectrumList);
00576 
00577     // compare 'a' and 'c'
00578 
00579     diff(a,c);
00580     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00581     unit_assert(!diff);
00582 
00583     // remove SpectrumList from a, and compare to b 
00584 
00585     a.spectrumListPtr.reset();
00586     diff(a, b);
00587     unit_assert(!diff);
00588 }

00819 void testMSData()
00820 {
00821     if (os_) *os_ << "testMSData():\n";
00822 
00823     MSData a;
00824     initializeTestData(a);
00825 
00826     // write 'a' out to a stream
00827 
00828     ostringstream oss;
00829     XMLWriter writer(oss);
00830     IO::write(writer, a);
00831     if (os_) *os_ << oss.str() << endl;
00832 
00833     // read 'b' in from stream, ignoring SpectrumList (default)
00834 
00835     MSData b;
00836     istringstream iss(oss.str());
00837     IO::read(iss, b); // IO::IgnoreSpectrumList
00838 
00839     // compare 'a' and 'b'
00840 
00841     Diff<MSData> diff(a,b);
00842     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00843     unit_assert(diff);
00844     unit_assert(diff.a_b.run.spectrumListPtr.get());
00845     unit_assert(diff.a_b.run.spectrumListPtr->size() == 1);
00846     unit_assert(diff.a_b.run.spectrumListPtr->spectrum(0)->userParams.size() == 1);
00847 
00848     // read 'c' in from stream, reading SpectrumList 
00849 
00850     MSData c; 
00851     iss.seekg(0);
00852     IO::read(iss, c, IO::ReadSpectrumList);
00853 
00854     // compare 'a' and 'c'
00855 
00856     diff(a,c);
00857     if (diff && os_) *os_ << "diff:\n" << diff << endl;
00858     unit_assert(!diff);
00859 
00860     // remove SpectrumList from a, and compare to b 
00861 
00862     a.run.spectrumListPtr.reset();
00863     diff(a, b);
00864     unit_assert(!diff);
00865 }
